TITLE: Tesla reported 466,140 deliveries for the second quarter, and production of 479,700 vehicles
SUMMARY: Tesla just posted its second-quarter vehicle production and deliveries report for 2023.

TITLE: Elon Musk says Twitter will temporarily limit number of posts users can view per day, citing 'system manipulation'
SUMMARY: Thousands of users received error messages while attempting to access Twitter on Saturday.

TITLE: What next for Wagner? Russia’s Putin battles to regain control after short-lived revolt
SUMMARY: The Wagner rebellion has left many observers of Russia's war in Ukraine asking what next for the group's future, both in Europe and across the globe.

TITLE: West Coast port workers in Canada officially begin strike
SUMMARY: The union delivered notice of its strike, which was approved by members last month, earlier this week.

TITLE: A shipping emissions showdown stands in the way of one of the biggest climate deals of the decade
SUMMARY: The U.N.'s International Maritime Organization is expected to update its current shipping emissions target, but many are concerned about the pace of the cuts.

TITLE: Finland is home to the world's happiest people. Their No. 1 secret is this 500-year-old mindset, says psychology expert
SUMMARY: For six years in a row, Finland has been ranked as the No. 1 happiest country in the world. Psychology expert E. Elisabet Lahti credits this phenomenon to "sisu," a Finnish mindset that has been around for more than years.

TITLE: Netherlands, home to a critical chip firm, follows U.S. with export curbs on semiconductor tools
SUMMARY: The Netherlands on Friday announced new export restrictions on advanced semiconductor equipment amid U.S. pressure to cut China off from key chipmaking tools.

TITLE: Marlboro maker Altria’s bet on smoke-free products
SUMMARY: Altria says it wants to help smokers transition away from cigarettes to what it calls "reduced harm alternatives" such as e-cigarettes.

TITLE: Apple's market cap closes above $3 trillion for the first time ever
SUMMARY: Apple's market cap topped $3 trillion on Friday, passing the $190.73 share price required to hit the milestone.

TITLE: Supreme Court strikes down Biden's student loan forgiveness plan
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court on Friday struck down President Biden's student loan forgiveness plan, denying millions of Americans up to $20,000 of debt relief.

TITLE: Euro zone inflation slides more than expected in June, but core rate ticks higher
SUMMARY: Euro zone inflation came in at 5.5% in June, according to preliminary data, lower than analyst expectations.

TITLE: The biggest takeaways from Microsoft's courtroom showdown with the FTC over Activision Blizzard
SUMMARY: Many internal Microsoft documents have come up in conversations with executives or have been released as part of a hearing over its Activision Blizzard deal.

TITLE: Google will block Canadian news outlets from search results in the country
SUMMARY: The move, like Meta's, comes after Canada's parliament passed a law requiring the two companies to pay fees to news outlets for linking to their content.

TITLE: Four North American cities now near worst air quality in the world
SUMMARY: New York; Washington, D.C.; Montreal; and Toronto have some of the worst air quality in the world.

TITLE: Key Fed inflation measure shows prices rose just 0.3% in May
SUMMARY: The personal consumption expenditures price index excluding food and energy was expected to increase 0.3% in May and 4.7% from a year ago.

TITLE: Korean telco giant adds ChatGPT tech to its A.I. chatbot, says you can talk to it like a 'close friend'
SUMMARY: SK Telecom, one of South Korea's biggest mobile carriers, upgraded its chatbot and added a feature powered by the technology behind ChatGPT.

TITLE: Goldman in talks to offload Apple credit card, savings products to American Express, source says
SUMMARY: Goldman Sachs is looking to unload its Apple financial products as part of a wider retreat from its failed consumer banking initiatives.

TITLE: Chinese e-commerce giant Alibaba expands number of physical grocery stores ahead of the unit's IPO
SUMMARY: Groceries have become a battleground for China's two biggest e-commerce firms: Alibaba and JD.com.

TITLE: China’s factory activity shrinks for a third month as recovery momentum stalls
SUMMARY: China’s June manufacturing PMI came in line with market expectations for 49.0, while non-manufacturing PMI was its weakest this year.

TITLE: Israel's Netanyahu concerned its defense systems may reach Iran if sent to Ukraine
SUMMARY: Israel's Benjamin Netanyahu hinted that if defense systems used by Ukrainian forces were to fall into Russian hands, they could end up in Iran.

TITLE: Compliance chief at Chinese fintech company stole girlfriend's insider info to trade VMware, tech stocks
SUMMARY: The head of compliance for a Chinese fintech company pleaded guilty to federal insider trading charges.

TITLE: China's Shein denies U.S. IPO rumors
SUMMARY: Chinese fast fashion giant Shein denies a Reuters report that said it has filed for an initial public offering in the U.S.

TITLE: China's previous monetary stimulus 'just isn't working,' a private survey shows
SUMMARY: China Beige Book's latest survey suggests rate cuts by the People's Bank of China in August may have had limited effect in spurring growth.

TITLE: Oil and gas will continue to power the world for decades to come, big oil firms say
SUMMARY: Oil and gas will remain leading sources of energy for decades to come on the back of a lagging energy transition, said key industry players at Energy Asia.

TITLE: Job interviews are getting longer — here’s why it could be a red flag
SUMMARY: "It may cause the candidate to think about how this reflects on the company's priorities ... communication, and the value it places on people," said one job seeker.

TITLE: CNBC Daily Open: The U.S. economy refuses to buckle
SUMMARY: Don’t fight the Fed, goes the saying in markets. Traders might want to add a new maxim: Don’t bet against the U.S. economy.

TITLE: First-quarter economic growth was actually 2%, up from 1.3% first reported in major GDP revision
SUMMARY: The U.S. economy showed much stronger-than-expected growth in the first quarter than previously thought.

TITLE: Tech IPO drought reaches 18 months despite Nasdaq's sharp rebound in first half of 2023
SUMMARY: Even with tech stocks rallying this year after a brutal 2022, internet and software companies are steering clear of the IPO market.

TITLE: Supreme Court rejects affirmative action at colleges as unconstitutional
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court ruling on affirmative action at Harvard and the University of North Carolina is a blow to efforts to boost enrollment of racial minorities.

TITLE: Sweden’s krona hits new record low as central bank hikes and plays down currency intervention
SUMMARY: The policy rate now sits at 3.75% and the figure is in line with forecasts made by analysts polled by Reuters.
